WinReg


WinReg package.  


Define main utility for manipulating registry:


 read, write and delete values

 create, delete keys
* list key and values


All function use Unicode

RegCreateKey(key::AbstractString) 
¶


Recursively create specified key. 

key
 can be specified using abbreviated form (e.g. 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE' -
 'HKLM').

Return 0 if key is existent, 1 if successful, -1 otherwise


source:


WinReg\src\regfunc.jl:190






RegDelete(key::AbstractString) 
¶


Delete specified 
key
. 

key
 can be specified using abbreviated form (e.g. 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE' -
 'HKLM').


view64
 specifies if key is 64 or 32 bit view (default); see https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa384129.aspx

If operation has success is returned 
true
, 
false
 otherwise

¶

key

nothing

Void
